The paper deals with the integration of rules and ontology knowledge bases, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and logic (cs.LO). The use of description logic programs and answer set semantics also suggests a connection to databases (cs.DB) and computational linguistics (cs.CL). Finally, the use of default logic as a foundation for query-based approaches suggests a connection to computational complexity (cs.CC).
